DocAttribute.Name: HasAssignments
DocAttribute.Documentation: Reference to the relationship objects, that assign (by an association relationship) other subtypes of IfcObject to this object instance. Examples are the association to products, processes, controls, resources or groups.

DocAttribute.Name: IsDecomposedBy
DocAttribute.Documentation: Reference to the decomposition relationship, that allows this object to be the composition of other objects. An object can be decomposed by several other objects.

DocAttribute.Name: Decomposes
DocAttribute.Documentation: References to the decomposition relationship, that allows this object to be a part of the decomposition. An object can only be part of a single decomposition (to allow hierarchical strutures only).

DocAttribute.Name: HasAssociations
DocAttribute.Documentation: Reference to the relationship objects, that associates external references or other resource definitions to the object.. Examples are the association to library, documentation or classification.
